    "summary": "Lourens van Dijk is an energetic, ambitious person and enjoys developing and implementing new renewable energy technologies. For more then ten years, he gained experience in solar energy research and developed a broad knowledge of the renewable energy market, in particular that of solar modules. During his PhD, he demonstrated a new method for external light trapping in solar modules. At Exasun, he developed innovative solar modules for building integration. As a creative researcher, he likes to create novel products in a dedicated team. He developed colored solar panels based on the Vibrant nanotechnology and founded Soluxa. Team Soluxa is currently developing the industrial production steps for fabricating colored solar panels. Colored solar panels will enable a renewable metamorphosis of the build environment.",
